So recently there's been a lot of these memes going around about #women tricking men with their #face, from make up, extreme contouring etc... As I've said, I think #MakeUp is an amazing #Artform, from stage & film fx, to making people feel amazing from injuries or skin ailments etc, effects from cancer etc, it's amazing and a real talent for the #artists....
...that said, in today's #society, teens are out with a full contoured face, like what happened to lip balm & clear #mascara (that's what it was in my day lol) 
So, inspired by @teamsolidtraining post, I made my own meme lol. #EnhanceYourFace #EnhanceYourBeauty #DontFakeToRemakeIt 
Simple! 
I'm generally an all natural girl, don't do fake nails, fake eyelashes & all dem ting (unless it's a fashion statement/photoshoot etc) but I do like a lil makeup sometimes... Mostly just concealer & mascara, I have bags, boo hoo lol. We're all human and beautiful in our natural States, that's where we need to feel the most #beautiful! So there's no need to always paint an entire new face on your face for no reason, just enhance what you've got. Or better yet wear none at all, at least no one will try to sue you for having different faces 😂lol #BelieveInYourBeauty #WhyDoKidsNeedMakeUp #RaiseQueens #Natural #Enhance #DontFakeIt

Kindness is tricky stuff, because it can’t be faked. You can’t force yourself to be kind—but you can relax yourself to be kind. That’s because kindness, empathy, compassion, love—these are fundamental to our being. When you see a puppy hurt, you instinctively share that pain and want to help. Only when we bury ourselves in preconceptions—thoughts—heightened emotions, or klesha in Buddhism—and pre-judgements (you know, prejudice) do we fail to see the sun of our basic goodness behind the clouds of our ego. But we can not, and should not, fight ego. Fighting is aggression, and that’s the problem. We can actually, simply, begin to do the hard work that is making friends with ourself. The payoff is huge—even when lonely, you’ll be with your best friend. You won’t lose countless hours and days to confusion, miserable self-obsession and “what about me.” You’ll relax, and smile, and open up, and help others—naturally. And that’s how we make America, or anywhere, kind again. We decide that caring is important. And to get there, we have only to meditate, to spend time in nature, to devote time to community and service, to use our hard-earned dollars to support ethical companies instead of those who would sell us on a better version of ourselves. The better version of yourself is right here, right now. You can’t buy it.
